# Coroot CE on OpenShift 4.18 Lab

Validated deployment guide and workaround for running **Coroot Community Edition** on **OpenShift 4.18.x** using Coroot Operator with a pinned custom node-agent.

---

# Overview

This repository provides a validated lab deployment for:

* Installing Coroot Operator via Helm
* Deploying Coroot backend on OpenShift 4.18
* Working around node-agent incompatibility on OCP 4.18
* Deploying demo workloads for observability validation
* Testing service maps, metrics, profiling, and RCA
* Deploying a Spring Boot application for Coroot validation
* Deploying traffic generators for observability testing
* Deploying Online Boutique microservices demo

---

# Validated Environment

| Component                   | Version  |
| --------------------------- | -------- |
| OpenShift                   | 4.18.38  |
| RHCOS Kernel                | 5.14.x   |
| Coroot Operator Helm Chart  | 0.9.4    |
| Coroot Operator App Version | 1.9.3    |
| Coroot Node Agent           | 1.28.3   |
| L7 Tracing                  | Disabled |

---

# Known Issue

Coroot Operator deploys a recent node-agent version by default.

On OpenShift 4.18 / RHCOS 5.14.x this may fail with:

```text
CrashLoopBackOff
verifier reject
permission denied loading BPF program
uprobes attach failure
```

---

# Root Cause

Newer Coroot node-agent versions (`>=1.31`) introduce:

* Advanced eBPF Programs
* TLS Uprobes
* OpenSSL Hooks
* Java TLS Hooks
* Deep Layer 7 Tracing

These features are incompatible with the tested OCP 4.18 kernel/verifier configuration.

---

# Validated Workaround

Use:

```yaml
Node Agent Version: 1.28.3
L7 Tracing: Disabled
Deployment Model: Custom DaemonSet
Operator Native Node-Agent: Disabled
```

---

